<item>
            <title>[LU-17616] &apos;lfs find&apos; has no way to search default directory layout</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-17616</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;It is not possible to use &quot;&lt;tt&gt;lfs find ...&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; to locate directories that have specific/bad default directory layouts on them.  This would be useful for finding directories that have e.g. default striped directories, which have caused many problems in the past, something like:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;# lfs find /mnt/testfs/* -type d --mdt-default --mdt-count +1 -print0 |
     xargs -0 lfs setdirstripe -d
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
